Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["\<\
Efficient Water - Cooled Bitter - Type Electromagnet for Zeeman Slowing in \
Cold - Atom Experiments\
\>", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.969618476631507*^9, 
  3.969618500934813*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4ae0aee9-9c5c-4470-b4f9-\
b4c05a95d8be"],

Cell["\<\
Rishav Koirala and Ben A. Olsen
2025\
\>", "Subtitle",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.969618492077821*^9, 
  3.969618506905809*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fbdf0130-c1b2-4ade-b6a0-\
ebb86e39abaa"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Thermal Measurements", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9696202322501383`*^9, 
  3.969620243093185*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ecc05f70-9b49-454f-89ae-\
3641f3b2cb3d"],

Cell["\<\
The FLIR thermal imaging camera produces .jpg files (in the thermal_data \
folder), and FLIR provides a software suite that can convert them to .csv \
files (https://www.flir.com/products/flir-thermal-studio-suite/?srsltid=\
AfmBOopCQmWCasnifR4ixrOgVXhfD0eWfw7VyX34fKqQ636rIWE7J8uU). While this is paid \
software, they seem to offer a free trial period. We suspect the images could \
be similarly analyzed using a python image analysis script.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9696214001919117`*^9, 
  3.969621544931386*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"85a59b5a-94e5-4659-a7d4-\
dd011b24b6b7"],

Cell["\<\
Import all the csv files produced for thermal images taken at various times \
since turning on the 200-A current in the coil.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.969620732719803*^9, 
  3.969620776063002*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"bd645bd2-425f-49d2-b9f8-\
158b22abe013"],

